Hi. 😋 Anyone up for a roadtrip to the beach? Let’s go! 🚗💕 What’s on your playlist? 🎶 

📸: Selfie from my last jaunt to the coast in December. Far too long ago.🤭

I had to sneak taking this pic because I knew as soon as he realized my camera was out, he’d yell, “MOM STOP!” …or “bruh,” depending on his mood. 

I looked over at him and saw an older boy that I didn’t know yesterday. 

He’s so smart & so wise. 
And a real pain in my ass sometimes. 

I think he’s absolutely beautiful. 🥹♥️

Reveling in all he’s becoming, but also deeply mourning the boy he’s outgrowing. 

Love you so much, Boo. ♥️

It’s a bird, it’s a plane… It’s #MakseInMexico ! 

The girls and I went to Mayan Cenotes yesterday and went on a bunch of different zip lines, snorkeled and got nibbled on by fish (loved it!), swan in caves with bats (they cute), canoed through a lagoon, and rock jumped into Cenotes. It ended with an authentic Mayan meal that may be the best food any of us have ever had. It was a magical day with my people. 🥰

We are collecting photos to a shared folder… more pics/vids to come!

Team Mäksē in Mexico! What an amazing time with all of these beautiful people. I’m so grateful for each an every one of them and all they do to help make @makse.life what it is today. There’s absolutely no way I could have done it on my own. Their hearts, innovation, care + concern for our community, and love for all shines in everything they do. And we all love each other BIG (that’s the best part 🥰). To me, they are family. ♥️

Love you, team! Thank you for helping create memories of a lifetime. 🫶🏼
“You do not find a happy life, you make it” 🤍

The boys went on a private tour of the California State Capitol and pretended they had a seat on the legislative floor, thanks to my amazing friend @mynameismariasn. 

I HAVE to brag on this friend of mine for a second: Not only is she the Director of the Assembly of Democrats, her office is directly across from @gavinnewsom (hello, corner office with a window view!), but she runs the entire Democratic Caucus as a Mexican expat, is multi-lingual (4 languages!!) and has a BA in Political Science, AND a Masters and PhD in International Relations and Affairs. (I seriously LOVE when she gets fired up about something! ✊🏾✊🏽✊🏼). She’s also a hellova cook who somehow has the capacity to send dinner our way during launch season. She’s basically a bonafide #badass.

Not only all of that, but she’s truly one of the most thoughtful, loyal, and bestest friends I could ask for. 

Love you so much, Maria! Thanks for giving the boys this experience. 🥰

My bestie for the next 11 days. IG, meet Bernie. Him’s kewt. 🥰 

Apologies in advance for the copious amounts of Bernie stories coming your way.

Girls trip to San Francisco in the Jeep! 
✌🏼😎

#SeasonOfYes @makse.life

That’s a wrap—2024 Photoshoot for @makse.life is done! 📸

Our photographer @kelseyowencreative asked me how long we’ve been in business and it was crazy to say, “this is our 5th launch.” 🤯 

I think we’ve finally found our stride with things (after MANY speed bumps as a start-up!) and am so thankful for my team, our freelancers who help fill in the gaps where we need them, our amazing Affiliates + Partners, and *especially* the #MakseFam, who have supported this dream of mine over the last 4 years. 

I’m so incredibly grateful that this is my job, that we get to learn + grow together in community, and live our best lives… while fully embracing the messy bits (hello, Pandemic & Co. 😏). 

I’m excited for this launch and everything else we have coming up in the next year as we expand even further into journaling, personal growth, and tools + accessories that help you stay organized, fulfilled, and focused on what truly matters. 

Thank you from the bottom of my heart for your support. 🫶🏼

Love you all. xx Sierra

“Family is more than blood. It’s the people in your life who want you in theirs; the ones who accept you for who you are. The ones who would do anything to see you smile, and who love you no matter what.” -Unknown

The last couple of years have brought so.much.loss. and when I look back at the people who were first to show up on my doorstep when I retreated from despair, the ones who sat supportively by my side and never judged me as I fell apart, the ones who never let me forget the blessings in my life no matter how overwhelmed I felt by everything… this woman has been the most steadfast through it all. 

She’s cared for my kiddos and helped manage my life when I gave birth to my third baby @makse.life, and has been by my side stuffing thousands of boxes, helping support my dream, and has wiped more tears than I can count. There’s really nothing she doesn’t know about me, and nothing I wouldn’t gladly share (don’t really have a choice—she helps me manage my correspondence and reads all my emails 😆).

I’ve watched her enter the workforce as a new college grad, get married, move, move, move again, have TWO beautiful babies, start a business, chase dreams, and change careers. The amount of life events we’ve shared in the last 5 years is truly wild.

🤍 

To watch you grow your beautiful family and to be there to fall in love with your kiddos during the first hours they spend in this world is a deep honor to me, @missyjune.

Congratulations on baby Jake, and becoming a party of four, Melissa! He’s every bit of amazing as you + Justin, and I look forward to loving him with all of my Auntie heart. 🥰
Love you BIG.

Sierra Friend ♥️ Life Coach, Founder + CEO of MäksēLife @makse.life 
📍Sacramento, CA
